    @allure.feature("Student Management")
    @allure.story("Class Filtering")
    def test_all_classes_filter(class_filter_page):
        """Test filtering students by all available class levels"""
        # Initialize tracking variables
        cycles_and_niveaux = []
        classes_tested = []
        classes_with_students = []
        classes_without_students = []
        classes_with_mismatches = []
    
        # Start processing from item 1
        current_index = 1
        processed_count = 0
        max_items = 100  # Safety limit
    
        # Process items one by one
        while processed_count < max_items:
            try:
                with allure.step(f"Processing sidebar item {current_index}"):
                    # Get the current sidebar item
                    item, title, has_caret = class_filter_page.get_sidebar_item(current_index)
    
                    # If item doesn't exist, we've reached the end
                    if not item:
                        break
    
                    # Process the item based on whether it has a caret icon
                    if has_caret:
                        # It's a cycle or niveau - just click to expand
                        class_filter_page.click_item(item, title, True)
                        cycles_and_niveaux.append(title)
    
                        # After expanding, refresh items by going back to the main page
                        # to avoid stale elements
                        class_filter_page.wait_for_page_loaded()
    
                        # Don't increment index - we want to start at the beginning
                        # after the DOM has changed
                    else:
                        # It's a class - click and test students
                        class_filter_page.click_item(item, title, False)
                        classes_tested.append(title)
    
                        # Wait for page to load
                        class_filter_page.wait_for_page_loaded()
    
                        # Check if there are students
                        if class_filter_page.has_students():
                            classes_with_students.append(title)
    
                            # Verify students
                            success, details = class_filter_page.verify_students_match_class(title)
    
                            if not success:
                                classes_with_mismatches.append(title)
                        else:
                            classes_without_students.append(title)
    
                        # Return to the main page
                        class_filter_page.wait_for_page_loaded()
    
                        # Increment the index for next item
                        current_index += 1
    
                    # Increment processed count
                    processed_count += 1
    
                    # Take a screenshot of the current state
>                   class_filter_page.page.screenshot(path=f"reports/screenshots/state_after_item_{current_index}.png")
